HARD LINKS: 
	Advantages:
		> Do not have single point of failure. 
	
	Disadvantages:
		> Not easy to see the target links.
		> Can link to files only within the same file system (partition).
		> Cannot be linked to directories.

SOFT LINKS: 
	Advantages:
		> Easier to see the target links.
		> Can link to any file (including across partitions).
	
	Disadvantages:
		> Have single point of failure.
